12. commutatis ordinibus in dextero latere] “Facing right about.'’ Jugurtha occupied the hill on the right of the Roman army as it descended the mountain.

13. 'triplicibus subsidiis] “In three linea supporting each other:” the usual Roman battle-array.

14. Transversis principiis] “With the first rank at right angles to the line of march.'' Principes are properly the second line, but principia the first rank of any line. The army having wheeled right about, continues to descend, in three columns, instead of, as before, in three lines.
